        <guid>https:/sysadmin.info.pl/en/blog/measuring-system-i-o/</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;To monitor system behavior, you need to start by creating a baseline that represents normal system behavior. You can do this using a tool like the sar command. You can then use tools such as netstat, iostat, lsof, w and uptime to monitor system behavior, comparing the results to the baseline to determine whether the system is experiencing problems.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
        
